The concrete issue is now clear: the collateral-share transfer reverts with `SenderNotSolventAfterTransfer()`. That means this deployed token implementation already blocks the “move collateral away while indebted” leg. I’m shifting the verifier to a debt-share route that first gives the recipient enough on-chain collateral to satisfy transfer-time solvency checks, then withdraws the original borrower’s collateral.
